  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 12:18",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Chronicles 12:18",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The Spirit came upon Amasai — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Not only saving graces, but other heroical and generous motions are ascribed to God’s Spirit, which here stirred up in him a more than ordinary greatness of mind and resolution. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thy God helpeth thee — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "We have seen evidences of God’s singular and gracious care of thee, and kindness to thee; and if we should oppose thee we should fight against God, and his word and providence. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Then David made them captains of the band — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Of those forces which they brought with them: or, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "he put them among the heads, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "officers of his band; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that is, he gave them commands, either now in his small army, each according to his quality; or afterward, when he was advanced to the kingdom: for it is not here said when he did this.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
